ASABA  – Police Operatives in Delta State Thursday busted the hideout of kidnapping gang in Owhorode- Udu, Udu Lo­cal Government Area of the state. Daily Independent gath­ered that a middle-aged man (name withheld) was kidnapped from his house to an unknown destination along with his vehicle by unknown armed men on January 12, 2022. It was learnt that the victim in a distressed call to the Otu-Jeremi Division on January 17, 2022 report­ed that he was kidnapped and he had escaped his ab­ductors at Owhorode Udu in Udu LGA. BREAKING: 3SC GM, Rasheed Balogun Dies At 62 JUST IN: Potiskum Grains Market Razed Down The DPO Ovwian-Alad­ja Division was immedi­ately contacted by the DPO Otu-Jeremi Division and on receipt of this informa­tion, he swiftly mobilised and led police operatives to the scene. It was gathered that the hoodlums fled their hideout on sighting the police. “Upon searching their hideout, the following ex­hibits were recovered; one cut to size locally made gun, one Beretta pistol with eight rounds of live ammu­nition, one handcuff, six as­sorted phones, nineteen(19) SIM cards, one UBA ATM card, one wristwatch, one jackknife and cash sum of thirty five thousand naira (N35, 000),” it was learnt. In a related develop­ment, police have nabbed a member of a robbery gang known for terrorising Sapele axis of Delta State. It was gathered that the Sapele Division received a distressed call that a two -man armed robbery gang were operating at No.6, Power Close, Okirigbaga in Sapele. POLL It was learnt that a de­tailed police patrol team was led by DPO Sapele Division, CSP Harrison Nwbuisi to the scene were suspects named Liyo Oki­ri ‘m’ age 25, was arrested and one locally made pistol, two live cartridges and one expanded cartridge were recovered.